	<div class="posts">
	<a name="106101096445938747">&nbsp;</a><br>
	<a href="http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/default.asp?url=/library/en-us/dnxmlweb/html/xmldocedit.asp">XML Editing: A WYSIWYG XML Document Editor</a>.&nbsp; An XML editor done as WYSIWYG using XSLT, and done in a browser.  There is an .hta that can be downloaded to work this puppy standalone.<br>
	<span class="byline">posted by Dennis at <a href="#106101096445938747">Friday, August 15, 2003</a></span></div>
